#!/usr/bin/env bash
# .githooks/pre-commit
#
# The pre-commit gate. Runs BEFORE commit-msg, so it can short-circuit
# obviously-broken commits without needing a message at all. The
# commit-msg hook is the protocol-gate enforcement step (it sees the
# message). This step enforces:
#
#   1. Repo typechecks across the workspace.
#   2. The `@docket/shared` test suite passes (it's the
#      validation-layer-of-record for branded types, scrubPII, trust-gate,
#      webhook verification).
#
# These are the cheapest possible checks that would have caught the
# "shipped 11 commits with broken types" failure mode. Tests for other
# packages run in CI but are too slow to gate every local commit.
#
# Bypass: `git commit --no-verify` (logged via the commit-msg hook
# unless that's also bypassed; CI catches both).
#
# 2026-05-15 audit (fragility sweep) caught the prior version of this
# script silently `exit 0`-ing when `bun` or `pnpm` was missing from
# PATH. On a fresh Windows dev machine without bun installed, EVERY
# commit was skipping the typecheck + shared-tests gates with only a
# small console warning the user might miss. Softer bypass than
# --no-verify, equally invisible. The user's mandate is "never skip
# the gates" -- so missing tools now HARD-FAIL with clear install
# instructions instead of silently passing.

set -e

if ! command -v pnpm >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  cat <<'EOM' >&2

[pre-commit] FAIL: pnpm not on PATH.

Typecheck depends on pnpm + turbo. The pre-commit gate cannot silently
skip; the audit caught that pattern as a Windows-machine bypass.

Install pnpm:
  - macOS / Linux: curl -fsSL https://get.pnpm.io/install.sh | sh -
  - Windows:       iwr https://get.pnpm.io/install.ps1 -useb | iex
  - npm fallback:  npm install -g pnpm@10.32.1

Then re-run the commit. For a genuine emergency where pnpm cannot be
installed (CI bootstrap, sandbox without network), use
`git commit --no-verify` and explain in the commit message body --
the bypass is auditable in git log + CI.

EOM
  exit 1
fi

echo "[pre-commit] typecheck (turbo)..."
pnpm typecheck >/dev/null 2>&1 || {
  echo "[pre-commit] typecheck FAILED. Run 'pnpm typecheck' to see errors."
  exit 1
}

if ! command -v bun >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  cat <<'EOM' >&2

[pre-commit] FAIL: bun not on PATH.

The @docket/shared test suite runs under bun (faster than node + has
the bun:test API). The pre-commit gate cannot silently skip; the
audit caught that pattern as a Windows-machine bypass.

Install bun:
  - macOS / Linux: curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
  - Windows:       powershell -c "irm bun.sh/install.ps1 | iex"
  - npm fallback:  npm install -g bun

Then re-run the commit. For a genuine emergency where bun cannot be
installed, use `git commit --no-verify` and explain in the commit
message body -- the bypass is auditable in git log + CI.

EOM
  exit 1
fi

echo "[pre-commit] @docket/shared tests (bun)..."
( cd packages/shared && bun test src ) >/dev/null 2>&1 || {
  echo "[pre-commit] @docket/shared tests FAILED. Run 'cd packages/shared && bun test src' to see errors."
  exit 1
}

echo "[pre-commit] OK."
